unused_trait_names = "warn"
use_self = "warn"
useless_let_if_seq = "warn"
useless_transmute = "warn"
verbose_file_reads = "warn"
wildcard_dependencies = "warn"
zero_sized_map_values = "warn"
comparison_chain = "allow"
should_panic_without_expect = "allow"
too_many_lines = "allow"
unwrap_used = "allow"
assigning_clones = "allow"
let_underscore_must_use = "allow"
let_underscore_untyped = "allow"
manual_range_contains = "allow"
map_unwrap_or = "allow"
self_named_module_files = "allow"
significant_drop_tightening = "allow"
wildcard_imports = "allow"

[lints.rust.future_incompatible]
level = "warn"
priority = -1

[lints.rust.nonstandard_style]
level = "warn"
priority = -1

[lints.rust.rust_2018_idioms]
level = "warn"
priority = -1

[lints.clippy.all]
level = "warn"
priority = -1

[package.metadata.docs.rs]
all-features = true
rustdoc-args = [ "--generate-link-to-definition",]

[[bench]]
name = "benchmarks"
harness = false

[package]
name = "flash-lso"
version = "0.6.0"
authors = [ "CUB3D <callumthom11@gmail.com>",]
description = "Fast and safe SOL/AMF0/AMF3 parsing. Supports serde, Adobe flex and cyclic references"
repository = "https://github.com/CUB3D/rust-sol"
readme = "README.md"
license = "MIT"
keywords = [ "sol", "amf", "parser", "serializer", "flash",]
edition = "2021"
categories = [ "data-structures", "encoding", "parser-implementations",]

[dependencies]
nom = "7.1.3"
enumset = "1.1.5"
thiserror = "2.0.3"

[dev-dependencies]
pretty_assertions = "1.4.0"
serde_json = "1.0.128"
criterion = "0.5.1"

[features]
default = [ "amf3",]
flex = []
serde = [ "dep:serde", "enumset/serde",]
all = [ "serde", "flex",]
amf3 = []

[dependencies.serde]
version = "1.0.210"
optional = true
features = [ "derive", "rc",]

[lints.rust.unexpected_cfgs]
level = "warn"
check-cfg = [ "cfg(fuzzing)",]

[workspace]
resolver = "2"
members = [ "derive",]

[package]
name = "gc-arena"
description = "safe, incrementally garbage collected arenas"
version = "0.5.3"
authors = [ "kyren <catherine@kyju.org>", "moulins", "Aaron Hill <aa1ronham@gmail.com>",]
edition = "2024"
license = "MIT"
readme = "README.md"
repository = "https://github.com/kyren/gc-arena"

[features]
default = [ "std",]
std = []
tracing = [ "dep:tracing",]
allocator-api2 = [ "dep:allocator-api2", "hashbrown?/allocator-api2",]

[dev-dependencies]
rand = "0.8"
trybuild = "1.0"

[workspace.package]
version = "0.5.3"
authors = [ "kyren <catherine@kyju.org>", "moulins", "Aaron Hill <aa1ronham@gmail.com>",]
edition = "2024"
license = "MIT"
readme = "README.md"
repository = "https://github.com/kyren/gc-arena"

[dependencies.allocator-api2]
version = "0.2"
optional = true
default-features = false
features = [ "alloc",]

[dependencies.gc-arena-derive]
path = "./derive"
version = "0.5.3"

[dependencies.hashbrown]
version = "0.15.2"
optional = true
default-features = false

[dependencies.tracing]
version = "0.1.37"
optional = true
default-features = false

[package]
name = "gc-arena-derive"
description = "proc-macro support for gc-arena"
version = "0.5.3"
authors = [ "kyren <catherine@kyju.org>", "moulins", "Aaron Hill <aa1ronham@gmail.com>",]
edition = "2024"
license = "MIT"
readme = "README.md"
repository = "https://github.com/kyren/gc-arena"

[lib]
proc-macro = true

[dependencies]

[dependencies.syn]
